A random number is basically a calculated number.
The computer has a specific formula (algorithm) that it uses to generate a number. This formula requires a seed to make the number different each time. In general, current time is used to make a unique random number.
For example : Say the formula is : RanNumber = seed + 2;
If seed was 5, then the answer would be 7. But to make it random, we can use the current time in milliseconds from what computer interprers the start of time in milliseconds (roughly around 1970s).
So ranNumber = 1029828227373792(made this # up) + 2;

